cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as 3D human pose estimation, 3D structure and egomotion estimation, facial image transformation using super-resolution and inpainting renderers. It proposes a weakly supervised neural network model that combines feedback from rendering predictions with distribution matching between predictions and a collection of ground-truth factors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks and adversarial training, which are covered in categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with graphics-related tasks such as image-to-image translation and rendering, which are covered in cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
